# Why: When `/template/use` creates a document from a template that has AcroForm
#      widgets baked into its PDF (the BizRethink AcroForm-pivot pipeline —
#      Cowork's apply_acroform_to_docx.py + inject_acroform_widgets.py output —
#      used for ISO PRA / Subscription / FRPA / Maverick), Documenso's
#      `createDocumentFromTemplate` calls `putNormalizedPdfFileServerSide` with
#      no options, which defaults `flattenForm: true`. That triggers
#      `normalizePdf → form.flatten()` on the document's AcroForm.
#
#      Verified bug: pdf-lib (`@libpdf/core`)'s `form.flatten()` mis-renders
#      multi-page multi-instance AcroForm widgets. Only the LAST content page's
#      widgets render with the correct values; widgets on earlier pages receive
#      jumbled values from other widgets (and the rendering also leaves stale
#      `<F:NAME>` marker text and underscore decorations in the flattened text
#      stream).
#
#      Two flatten sites must be patched (both call `putNormalizedPdfFileServerSide`
#      with no options, defaulting to flattenForm: true):
#        1. `packages/lib/server-only/template/create-document-from-template.ts:493`
#           — at /template/use time, when duplicating the template's PDF for the
#           new document.
#        2. `packages/lib/server-only/document/send-document.ts:355`
#           — at distribute time, in `injectFormValuesIntoDocument`, called from
#           `sendDocument` whenever envelope.formValues exists. This is the
#           SECOND flatten — the document gets re-filled and re-normalized at
#           every send. Initially missed; verified live: even with site (1)
#           patched, document 17 came out flattened because (2) re-flattened.
#
#      Diagnosed against ISO PRA (template id=8, document id=16) — sealed PDF
#      page 2 had: effective_date widget rendered "TestPartner..." instead of
#      "2026-05-02"; iso_partner_company widget rendered "Shwet" instead of
#      "TestPartner ISO LLC"; commission_percentage widget rendered "Founder"
#      instead of "8". Page 5 sig block rendered all values correctly.
#
#      Single-page contracts (Payzli) are unaffected because all widgets land
#      on the only content page = the "last" page = the one pdf-lib renders
#      correctly. Bug is multi-page-only.
#
#      Fix: disable AcroForm flatten on document creation. AcroForm widgets
#      stay alive in the document with `/V` populated by `insertFormValuesInPdf`
#      (the immediately preceding step). PDF readers (and Documenso's Konva-
#      based signing-page renderer) display the filled values directly from
#      `/V` + `/DA` + `/DR/Font/HelvB` — same visible result, without going
#      through pdf-lib's broken flatten path. The cryptographic seal applied at
#      sign-completion (`packages/signing/index.ts:getSigner()` + the document
#      certificate) locks the document; AcroForm `/V` becomes immutable post-
#      seal because the seal-byte-range covers the full PDF including form
#      objects, exactly as intended for filled-then-signed documents.
#
#      Fragility: LOW-MED. The function `putNormalizedPdfFileServerSide`
#      already accepts an optional `{ flattenForm?: boolean }` second arg, so
#      we're using its public API. The only fragility is if upstream changes
#      the call signature or removes the option — caught at typecheck time
#      during the weekly upstream-sync.
#
#      Long-term: file an upstream issue + PR against pdf-lib (libpdf) to fix
#      the multi-page multi-instance flatten render bug. Until then, this
#      overlay is the cheapest reliable workaround.
#
diff --git a/packages/lib/server-only/template/create-document-from-template.ts b/packages/lib/server-only/template/create-document-from-template.ts
